The majority of men in Slovakia view abortion as a crime, and 60 percent of them would like to see it banned, according to a survey carried out by the Focus polling agency for the daily Sme.

The survey was carried out in the first half of September on a sample of 1,000 respondents. It showed that 60 percent of men and 51 percent of women would like to see abortion banned. The survey also showed that 60 percent of men and 51 percent of women would like to see the current law on abortion changed.
